Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the tagliatelle.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. When the pan is hot, add the @chorizo{60%g} and stir-fry until it starts to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the chorizo has started to brown, add the shallot and pepper and fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes} (add a little oil if needed). Continue to stir while it cooks. Add the garlic and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, then stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1} and @sugar{1} for the sauce, @chicken stock paste{15%g} and @chilli flakes{1%tsp} (use less if you don't like too much heat) to the pan. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g} to the boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Roughly chop the @chives{1}. In a large #bowl{}, mix together the @olive oil{1} for the dressing, the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}, @pepper{pinch} and sugar (if you have any). Set the dressing aside for now.

Once the tagliatelle is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @king prawns{225%g} and cook for another ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Season to taste with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat. Add the tagliatelle to the sauce and toss to coat.

Just before serving, add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the bowl with the dressing and toss to coat.

> TIP: Don't do this too early or the leaves will become soggy.

Divide the tagliatelle between your bowls and spoon over any remaining sauce. Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{25%g} and chives to finish, then serve with the pea shoot salad alongside. Enjoy!